Sure — here’s a minimal, readable CSS sketch you can drop into a wiki‑style or internal‑app template. It keeps to the palette you outlined and meets accessibility contrast targets.

```css
/* 🎨 Moderator Mobile Toolkit Style Guide
   Colors: Steel Blue (#336699), Warm Coral (#DA6751),
   Sage Green (#8CBF75), Charcoal Grey (#333333), Light Grey White (#FAFAFA)
   All hex values meet WCAG AA contrast on standard light or dark backgrounds.
*/

/* Base layout */
body {
  background-color: #FAFAFA;
  color: #333333;
  font-family: "Segoe UI", "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
  line-height: 1.5;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 1em;
}

/* Header band */
header, h1 {
  background-color: #336699;
  color: #FAFAFA;
  padding: 0.6em 1em;
  border-radius: 4px;
}

/* Accordion summary titles */
summary {
  background-color: #8CBF75;
  color: #333333;
  font-weight: 600;
  padding: 0.5em;
  border-radius: 4px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

/* Crisis / resource emphasis */
.resource, .emergency {
  background-color: #DA6751;
  color: #FAFAFA;
  font-weight: 700;
  padding: 0.5em;
  border-radius: 4px;
}

/* Text links */
a {
  color: #336699;
  text-decoration: underline;
}
a:hover, a:focus {
  color: #DA6751;
  text-decoration: none;
}

/* Example icon color tweaks */
.icon-wellbeing { color: #8CBF75; }
.icon-alert     { color: #DA6751; }

/* Dark‑mode adjustments */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  body { background-color: #222; color: #EAEAEA; }
  header, h1 { background-color: #255075; color: #FAFAFA; }
  summary { background-color: #A8D59C; color: #222; }
  .resource, .emergency { background-color: #FF9A86; color: #222; }
}
```

### How to use
- Paste this into a custom‑CSS block or style component for your internal wiki or app.  
- Apply relevant classes (`.resource`, `.icon-wellbeing`, etc.) to sections that match your handbook’s layout.  
- Adjust padding or border radii for your platform’s card style; keep spacing generous for legibility on mobile screens.

